# ============================================================================
# security.list  --  Corvid OS arm64 / Pi 5  curated security / pentest catalog
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Plain package list for the Pi build (provisioning/build-pi5.sh feeds it to
# `apt install` on the arm64 rootfs). RULES for this file (do not break them):
#   * ONE package per line.
#   * '#' comments must be on their OWN line. A trailing "pkg  # note" would be
#     passed to apt verbatim and break the install, so every comment here is a
#     full line starting with #.
#
# CURATION APPROACH (why this list looks the way it does)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This is the ARM analog of the amd64 config/package-lists/security.list.chroot.
# The base is Ubuntu 24.04 LTS (noble) arm64 + kubuntu-desktop. Ubuntu builds
# its `universe` component for arm64, and the VAST MAJORITY of these tools are
# C, Python, Perl, Ruby, or Go programs that Ubuntu compiles for arm64 exactly
# as it does for amd64. So the curated list ports 1:1 -- the same ~84 tools,
# same categories, installed from the pinned Ubuntu base, NOT from Kali.
#
# KALI-ONLY TOOLS ARE NOT BAKED IN HERE (identical policy to amd64).
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Well-known tools Ubuntu does NOT package (metasploit-framework, seclists,
# exploitdb/searchsploit, the social-engineer-toolkit, crackmapexec/netexec,
# responder, wpscan, sslyze, theHarvester, enum4linux, feroxbuster,
# volatility3, and other Kali-exclusives) are deliberately LEFT OUT of this
# build. On arm64 they are offered on-demand by the RUNTIME INSTALLER, which
# pulls them from the low-priority, pinned KALI arm64 fallback repo. That repo,
# its keyring, and its pin are the SAME dormant runtime fallback the amd64 image
# ships (config/hooks/0900-kali-runtime-repo.chroot +
# config/includes.chroot/etc/apt/keyrings/kali-archive-keyring.gpg), except the
# arm64 build sources Kali's arm64 packages. See the "KALI arm64 FALLBACK"
# catalog at the bottom of this file for the known names.
# ============================================================================


# ============================================================================
# Network discovery & scanning
# ============================================================================
nmap
masscan
netdiscover
arp-scan
fping
hping3
netcat-openbsd
socat
tcpdump
p0f
netsniff-ng

# ============================================================================
# DNS enumeration & host/OSINT recon
# ============================================================================
# dnsutils is the familiar transitional name; bind9-dnsutils is the concrete
# package that ships dig/nslookup/host in noble. Both are kept for safety.
dnsutils
bind9-dnsutils
whois
dnsrecon
dnsenum
fierce
dmitry

# ============================================================================
# Web application testing
# ============================================================================
nikto
sqlmap
wfuzz
dirb
dirsearch
gobuster
ffuf
whatweb
wapiti
wafw00f
cadaver

# ============================================================================
# Password attacks & hash cracking
# ============================================================================
john
# hashcat: the arm64 package installs and runs fine, but a Pi 5 has no practical
# OpenCL GPU backend, so cracking falls back to the CPU (much slower than a
# desktop GPU). This is a PERFORMANCE note, not an availability gap -- the
# package is genuinely arm64, so it stays in the baked-in set.
hashcat
hydra
medusa
ncrack
patator
hashid
crunch
cewl
ophcrack
chntpw

# ============================================================================
# Wireless auditing (802.11 / WPS)
# ============================================================================
reaver
pixiewps
hcxtools
hcxdumptool
macchanger
hostapd

# ============================================================================
# Sniffing, spoofing & MITM
# ============================================================================
wireshark
tshark
ettercap-graphical
bettercap
dsniff
tcpflow
driftnet
arpwatch
yersinia

# ============================================================================
# SMB / SNMP / network-service enumeration
# ============================================================================
smbclient
smbmap
snmp
onesixtyone
nbtscan
ldap-utils

# ============================================================================
# Forensics, steganography & file recovery
# ============================================================================
sleuthkit
autopsy
foremost
scalpel
testdisk
binwalk
steghide
libimage-exiftool-perl

# ============================================================================
# Reverse engineering & debugging
# ============================================================================
radare2
gdb
ltrace
strace
checksec

# ============================================================================
# Anonymity, proxying & tunneling
# ============================================================================
tor
torsocks
proxychains4
stunnel4
openvpn
wireguard-tools


# ============================================================================
# arm64-unavailable, covered by the Kali arm64 runtime fallback
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NONE of the curated Ubuntu tools above needed to be moved here. Every package
# in this list is built for arm64 in Ubuntu noble (main/universe), so the amd64
# catalog ports to the Pi 1:1. This section is kept as an explicit landing spot:
# if the build's dry-run against the real arm64 apt cache ever reports a package
# as "not built for arm64", MOVE it below this line (do not delete it) and let
# the Kali arm64 runtime fallback supply it at runtime instead, e.g.:
#     sudo apt update
#     sudo apt install -t kali-rolling <tool>
#   aircrack-ng   (dropped from Ubuntu 24.04 arm64; Kali arm64 carries it)
#   bully         (Kali-only WPS attack tool)
#   mdk4          (Kali-only wifi tool)
#   wifite        (depends on aircrack-ng; get it from Kali arm64 at runtime)


# ============================================================================
# KALI arm64 FALLBACK CATALOG  (NOT installed by this list -- reference only)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The names below are the well-known Kali-exclusive tools that are NOT in
# Ubuntu noble. Do NOT uncomment them here -- baking Kali packages into the
# image risks library skew against the Ubuntu base. Install them at RUNTIME
# from the pinned, dormant Kali arm64 fallback repo instead:
#     sudo apt update
#     sudo apt install -t kali-rolling metasploit-framework
# apt resolves them from Kali arm64 (pinned low) while every core lib stays on
# Ubuntu. Kali maintains strong arm64 coverage, so these resolve on the Pi.
#
# Exploitation / frameworks:
#   metasploit-framework
#   exploitdb                 # provides searchsploit; not in noble
#   set                       # social-engineer-toolkit
#   beef-xss
#   commix
#
# Credential / AD / SMB attack:
#   crackmapexec              # a.k.a. netexec on newer Kali
#   responder
#   enum4linux
#
# Web:
#   wpscan
#   feroxbuster
#   skipfish
#
# Recon / OSINT (upstream Go/py tools Ubuntu does not package):
#   theharvester
#   amass
#   subfinder
#   nuclei
#
# TLS / crypto analysis:
#   sslyze
#
# Wireless / RF:
#   kismet
#
# Forensics / memory:
#   volatility3
#   bulk-extractor
#
# Wordlists / payloads:
#   seclists
#   wordlists                 # Kali metapackage; no Ubuntu equivalent
#   nishang
#   powersploit
# ============================================================================
